---
description: Naming conventions for microservices, APIs, and events
alwaysApply: true
---

microservices-naming-conventions:

- Service names: lowercase kebab-case (e.g., user-service, order-processor)
- REST endpoints: plural nouns, kebab-case (e.g., /api/v1/user-profiles)
- Event names: past-tense domain events (e.g., OrderPlaced, UserRegistered)
- gRPC methods: PascalCase verbs (e.g., GetUser, CreateOrder)
- Message queue topics: {domain}.{entity}.{action} (e.g., orders.order.placed)
- Environment variables: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., DATABASE_URL, SERVICE_PORT)
- Docker images: {org}/{service-name}:{semver} (e.g., acme/user-service:1.2.3)
